<br>
When soloing in the deep I was still learning the lay of the land and was zoning a lot.  Normally I would equip a muzzle, two daggers, the armor, then a shawl (I was waiting on a group so wasn't too concerned with whether or not any of it actually helped) and I would always see the daggers.  One time after I zoned I gave it the armor first, and I couldn't see the daggers once they were equipped and after reading a theory that pets only had four slots, I figured that's what happened.<br>
<br>
Is there any way to tell if armor helps? <br>
<br>
Yes, but I wouldn't trust any tests done with less than 20 or so fights.<br>
<br>
Is there any way to tell if resists help?<br>
<br>
Anything short of a Verant employee stating that they do won't convince me, checking the resist rate of a pet with the current random system of EQ would be extremely difficult, if not impossible.<br>
<br>
